      "body": "**Blueprint defect: duplicate `\\label{thm:albanese_universal_property}` across two chapters.**\n\nTwo active theorem environments share the label, pointing at different Lean decls \u2014 a leanblueprint collision (`\\cref` resolves ambiguously; one node shadows the other in the DAG).\n\n- `Albanese_AlbaneseUP.tex:99` \u2192 `\\lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Pic0.albanese_universal_property}` (Route-A target; decl **exists** but is `sorryAx`-tainted \u2014 its `\\leanok` was **false and removed this run**). 7 in-file `\\cref`s.\n- `Jacobian.tex:490` \u2192 `\\lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.Pic.albaneseUP}` (north-star; that decl **does not exist** in AJC Lean \u2014 honest forward-pointer, no `\\leanok`). 3 in-file `\\cref`s.\n\n**Why it matters:** same statement, two encodings, one label \u2192 the compiled DAG merges them and crefs cross-resolve. Not blocking T9 (Lean-side).\n\n**Suggested fix (deferred, needs design-aware cref surgery):** give the `Jacobian.tex` north-star node a distinct label (e.g. `thm:albanese_universal_property_northstar`) and repoint its 3 in-file crefs; keep `thm:albanese_universal_property` for the Route-A node. Left unfixed this round to avoid guessing the intended DAG edge (does the north-star `\\uses` the Route-A theorem, or restate it?).",
